By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – As Nigeria joins the rest of the countries to mark the World Youth Skill Day, the Presidential candidate of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) has tasked the young people to learn a skill that will get them a good paying job and enable them set up their business and be their own boss. The former Vice President who stated this via his verified twitter handle @atiku said: “On this World Youth Skills Day, I wish to impress on our young people the need to learn a skill that puts you at an advantage to get a good-paying job and the opportunity to set up your business and be your own boss.’ “By the way, such a skill that can also help you with a side hustle. -AA”. Sundiata Post recalls that 15th July is a day set aside world over to mark the World Youth Skill Day. By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - As an ongoing effort to help the youths of Africa disentangle from the shackles of the third world bondage, Joseph Joseph Etim and the entire team of Young People Connect is organizing a Connect Conference tagged, 'Hacking Skills And Opportunities Beyond Borders'. Young… In "Entertainment" Abuja (Sundiata Post) - President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday, urged youths to acquire knowledge not towards getting government jobs as there are no “jobs in government anymore.”He also urged youths to acquaint themselves with history to avoid making the same mistakes of the past.According to a statement signed on Wednesday… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Renowned American boxer and boxing promoter, Floyd Mayweather wants to establish a boxing academy in Africa, especially in Nigeria to build young fighters. Mayweather, a former WBC Super featherweight champion said this when he visited frontline All Progressives Congress (APC) Presidential Aspirant and Minister… In "Top Stories"